{"parse":{"title":"Female Infanticide Prevention Act, 1870","pageid":33012321,"revid":761234838,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"width:22em\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold\">Female Infanticide Prevention Act, 1870 (Act VIII of 1870)</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/File:British_Raj_Red_Ensign.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"British Raj Red Ensign.svg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/be/British_Raj_Red_Ensign.svg/150px-British_Raj_Red_Ensign.svg.png\" width=\"150\" height=\"75\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/be/British_Raj_Red_Ensign.svg/225px-British_Raj_Red_Ensign.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/be/British_Raj_Red_Ensign.svg/300px-British_Raj_Red_Ensign.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"600\" data-file-height=\"300\" /></a><div><a href=\"/wiki/British_India\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"British India\">British India</a> under <a href=\"/wiki/British_Raj\" title=\"British Raj\">Crown rule</a></div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\nAn Act for the Prevention of the murder of Female Infants .</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Enacted by</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Governor-General_of_India\" title=\"Governor-General of India\">Governor-General of India</a> in Council</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Date enacted</th><td>\n18 March 1870</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>The <b>Female Infanticide Prevention Act, 1870</b>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> also <b>Act VIII of 1870</b> was a <a href=\"/wiki/Legislative_act\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Legislative act\">legislative act</a> passed in <a href=\"/wiki/British_India\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"British India\">British India</a>, to prevent murder of female infants. The Section 7 of this Act declared that it was initially applicable only to the territories of <a href=\"/wiki/Oudh_State\" title=\"Oudh State\">Oudh</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/North-Western_Provinces\" title=\"North-Western Provinces\">North-Western Provinces</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Punjab_Province_(British_India)\" title=\"Punjab Province (British India)\">Punjab</a>, but the Act authorized the Governor General to extend the law to any other district or province of the <a href=\"/wiki/British_Raj\" title=\"British Raj\">British Raj</a> at his discretion.<sup id=\"cite_ref-fipa1_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-fipa1-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Text\">Text</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Female_Infanticide_Prevention_Act,_1870&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Text\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\">Main article: <a href=\"/wiki/Female_infanticide_in_India\" title=\"Female infanticide in India\">Female infanticide in India</a></div>\n<p>The British colonial authorities passed the <i>Female Infanticide Prevention Act 1870</i>, under pressure of Christian missionaries and social reformers seeking an end to the incidences of female infanticides in South Asia. The law's preamble stated that the murder of female infants is believed to be commonly committed in certain parts of British India, and these were Oudh, North-Western Provinces and Punjab.<sup id=\"cite_ref-fipa1_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-fipa1-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> The Act initially applied to these regions.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The law authorized the creation of a police force to maintain birth, marriage and death registers, to conduct census of the district at its discretion, enforce a special tax on the district to pay for the expenses and entertainment of said police officers.<sup id=\"cite_ref-fipa1_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-fipa1-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> The Act also stipulated a prison sentence of six months or a fine of thirty thousand rupees, or both, on anyone who disobeyed or obstructed the police officers enforcing the Act.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> Section 6 of the Act allowed the police officer to seize a child from any person he suspects may neglect or endanger any female child, as well as force collect a monthly fee from that person.<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Current_status\">Current status</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Female_Infanticide_Prevention_Act,_1870&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Current status\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The Act was in force till 1981 in Pakistan, when it was superseded by an ordinance.<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes\">Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Female_Infanticide_Prevention_Act,_1870&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Notes\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">\"Indian Short Titles Act (XIV), 1897\" in <cite class=\"citation book\">Government of India, Legislative Department (1899). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=-fIZAAAAYAAJ&amp;pg=PA337\"><i>The unrepealed general acts of the Governor General in Council: with chronological tables. From 1834 to 1903, both inclusive, Volume 6</i></a>. Calcutta: Superintendent of Govt. Printing. p.&#160;337<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">7 September</span> 2011</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+unrepealed+general+acts+of+the+Governor+General+in+Council%3A+with+chronological+tables.+From+1834+to+1903%2C+both+inclusive%2C+Volume+6&amp;rft.place=Calcutta&amp;rft.pages=337&amp;rft.pub=Superintendent+of+Govt.+Printing&amp;rft.date=1899&amp;rft.au=Government+of+India%2C+Legislative+Department&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3D-fIZAAAAYAAJ%26pg%3DPA337&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AFemale+Infanticide+Prevention+Act%2C+1870\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-fipa1-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-fipa1_2-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-fipa1_2-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-fipa1_2-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=OvYZAAAAYAAJ&amp;pg=PAPA165\">The Unrepealed General Acts of the Governor General in Council</a></i>, p. PA165, at <a href=\"/wiki/Google_Books\" title=\"Google Books\">Google Books</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Section 7 of <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=OvYZAAAAYAAJ&amp;pg=PAPA167\">The Unrepealed General Acts of the Governor General in Council</a></i>, p. PA167, at <a href=\"/wiki/Google_Books\" title=\"Google Books\">Google Books</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Section 2-4 of <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=OvYZAAAAYAAJ&amp;pg=PAPA166\">The Unrepealed General Acts of the Governor General in Council</a></i>, p. PA166, at <a href=\"/wiki/Google_Books\" title=\"Google Books\">Google Books</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Section 6 of <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=OvYZAAAAYAAJ&amp;pg=PAPA167\">The Unrepealed General Acts of the Governor General in Council</a></i>, p. PA167, at <a href=\"/wiki/Google_Books\" title=\"Google Books\">Google Books</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Tahir Wasti, The Application of Islamic Criminal Law in Pakistan: Sharia in Practice, p. 140 footnote 137, BRILL Netherlands (2009)</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"/wiki/File:Hourglass.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Stub icon\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b6/Hourglass.svg/20px-Hourglass.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"33\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b6/Hourglass.svg/30px-Hourglass.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b6/Hourglass.svg/40px-Hourglass.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"189\" data-file-height=\"315\" /></a></td><td><i>This history article is a <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Stub\" title=\"Wikipedia:Stub\">stub</a>. You can help Wikipedia by <a class=\"external t